reviews.text:
It was family time again and it was great. The wait is long during the weekend up to 20+.  Our bartender was very attentive to our table and our needs. The kitchen made sure all our food came out together. It was a nice environment, family friendly. One of our server didn't want to give us an extra order of corn muffins...not sure why.
No one complained about the quality and quantity of their meal.

The service was on point! We had Carlton as a waiter, and he was attentive and friendly. The drinks were delicious, they tasted like juice but carried a punch. The food was flavored well, and I feel like I had the right amount. The only thing I would change is appetizer portions. They were good, but they aren't really sharable. The manager, William, came to check on us, and it added a nice touch to the experience.

This is our go to place whenever we want some good soul food. Like the consistency in portions and taste. We have tried pretty much everything on the menu over the years.
Service has always been good. Long wait to be seated- yes, never fails 😂 but its worth it.
Parking is very convenient. There are street parking & nearby garage parking.

This was my first visit to Carolina Kitchen. Our server, Will, was so patient and attentive. The food was out of this world!! I had the three piece fried chicken meal with collards and sweet potatoes. I chose 3 wings. You can choose any 3 pieces. The wings were jumbo wings. They were crispy and well seasoned. I wanted to eat all three but couldn't. The greens and yams were also good and well complimented the chicken. The star of the meal was the cornbread muffins they give you. Just thinking about them...mmm! They were crispy on the edges and light and fluffy inside. The topping tasted like lemon honey butter. It was sheer perfection!
They have a cafeteria style line for takeout. There is table service for dining in. This restaurant is one of my new top restaurants in the DC area.

Came here for dinner on Sunday- first I would like to point out how I appreciate the business for being open and serving the public during this pandemic. Thank you.
Next I want to point out my experience with the Bar Tender Val, I remembered her name because my mom shares the same name. Val was more than amazing I watched her engage with other patrons and what I noticed was nothing other but stellar service. Now to the food.  “kiss the chef” the food was pretty good, hot, fresh and most importantly the portions great! Thank you again!

My boyfriend ordered a sub from here on Sunday and ended up with food poisoning. He’s still not feeling well. He can’t keep anything down. And he started not feeling well like a bit after he ate half his sub! Now he has missed work this week but now he’s going to miss out on Thanksgiving!

I ordered 3 subs from this location and was very disappointed.  When I cut into the sandwich there was barely any meat most of the sandwich was just a slice of cheese and tomato. If you happen to go in here please look at how they fix your sub because you will end up eating just a cheese and tomato sub.
The cleanest subway I’ve ever been to!
This is a new Subway but the food is fresh. The restaurant workers are friendly.

I came in after work a few days ago and the environment was very friendly. I was served by Teofila and we carried on a great conversation. She was very polite and answered every question I had. The service I was provided was terrific and will definitely tell family and friends to come here when they want delicious, fast, and  fresh food.

A classic restaurant for a great family dinner! Olive Garden has always been our go-to Italian restaurant. 🇮🇹

We usually order the chicken Alfredo pasta, and we choose the endless salad and garlic bread. Their garlic bread speaks for itself. 🥖♥️

I loved the atmosphere of this branch. I did notice that they didn’t have any music playing which was different from other restaurants. I would probably suggest they do that just because people’s voices and utensil sounds were a little too loud. Some background music would help with that.

Shout out to our waitress Juliza who was such a great and helpful server. 💯
This place was awesome. Great service, great food and drinks. Great prices, very affordable. $8 margaritas, $10 lunch specials and $6 lunch specials to go. Very beautiful atmosphere. Quick service.

I Always Come To This Location For Lunch , At This Point Im A Regular. I Really Enjoy The Staff Because They Are Always So Friendly & The Servers Are Always Attentive & Go The Extra Mile. The Food Is Always Amazing & Affordable. The SeaFood Alfredo Was Delicious ; The Scallops Were Delectable!!!! I Enjoyed The Italian Margarita. It Was A Beautifully Presented Cocktail.

The customer service was amazing. We did spend ah lot of time waiting for things we asked for, reason I rated 4 Stars, but other then that the atmosphere and people were pretty enjoyable considering we've been isolated for ages. This was ah great spot to visit in the midst of ah pandemic!
.
.
𝗚𝗿𝗲𝗮𝘁 𝗩𝗶𝗯𝗲𝘀 & 𝗧𝗶𝗺𝗲𝘀

As Italian I gave a go to spaghetti with salsa marinara and meatballs. I have to say that the taste of meatballs reminded me my nonna's one which I have not had since October last year. Very impressed. And staff was friendly too.

name: Dunkin'
vicinity: Metro Shops, 2970 Belcrest Center Drive Ste 112, Hyattsville

reviews.text: Iced coffee was way too creamy. Just tasted like milk with a drop of coffee.  Didn't taste the espresso; in fact, I don't even think they put it in there. Food tasted undercooked. 50% of the time there is an item missing. No big bag to hold everything in, only the little bag, so my food got cold fast.

Decent/Quality:
For the most part, should brighten up the lights at least. It definitely gave a feeling of "We're Closed", serive was great and a DD who know how to make a fine beverage as well.

I really wish I didn’t have to write this review but after todays experience I have to. Almost every morning I go to this Dunkin before work for iced coffee and egg and cheese wraps. I never order coffee sweetened but today it was. This usually isn’t a big deal to me but today it was because of the egg and cheese wraps. There was parchment paper melted in with the egg and cheese. Something tasted funny initially but I thought it was because I was recovering from a cold but when I looked down at it I was so disappointed.

I went back and showed them both the wraps and drinks. They didn’t apologize, the lady offered to make me a new drink. I said I just want my money back. She went to the back and came out with the cash to give me. Still no apology or complimentary drink/wraps.

I don’t think I will be returning there anytime soon. :(

UPDATE 2/08/2022: The manager Kurnal personally reached out to me about the incident and apologized. Asked me to come back In tomorrow and he will take care of me. He stopped by my work and gave me a dozen donuts. The only reason why I go to this location is because of Kurnal. He always makes sure I am happy and my order is correct. I have changed this review to 5 stars and Will definitely be going back for breakfast everyday!

Very unprofessional customer service. Experienced racism from Hispanic female. She told the 2 black people to use the kiosk and wouldn’t take their orders but instead took the orders of 2 other Hispanics very rude watch out for the racism

Always get my coffee orders wrong, always leave the cream cheese separated when I ask for it to be spread onto my bagel. Poor customer service & 1 extremely rude employee. Just lost 2 daily customers & definitely will loose more by the end of the month.
It was our first time eating here, delicious food, awesome service and family friendly!

I decided to stop by b4 I started shopping. Walked in and was seated in minutes. Ordered the dry wings and a salad. My son ordered the chicken platter. No soon as the lady walked away this guy came by and bought the wings back to the table… the first thing My son mentioned was “straight out the microwave!” I had to jokingly agreed.. im starving and I started eating the wings.. now I’m sitting here with an upset stomach. The waitress came over and I explained that situation with her n asked to speak with the manager. He came over n gave him the same speech, and he said the food was cooked to order… I told him unless it’s cooked within 2 minutes them wings were already there… he said he was gonna speak to the cooks and discount my meal. I told him that I don’t have a problem paying n agreed to pay it, but this shouldn’t happen to anyone else… AGREED!
Service was great. Food was good even tho the steak wasn’t well done like I asked 😒. Blackberry martinis were delicious as usual. Overall a great evening 🥰🙌🏾👨🏾‍🍳
My family got seated immediately. Waitress was super friendly and food was good and came fast. My only issue was that the Pina Koala was a bit too strong for my liking.

Ok, I always say that I am going to write a review. So Outback you got me! My server Jaye, was great too bad he works for a place that will hold him back. I am a Chef and would steal him from you guys in a minute. I ordered the Chicken and Shrimp Alfredo. I sent it back because it was cold. Who in there right mind would be ok with cold pasta that is suppose to be eaten hot. I am attaching pictures to show what I ordered and what I took home. I am tired of COVID-19 food. Stop asking for US to come out and support local businesses. I spoke with the manager before leaving and I got the same sorry I'll speak with the kitchen Staff. Almost forgot the had no Tequila for any margaritas, and there were drink specials. SMH... Now I have to go home and remix my whole meal. #DidNotFeelLikeCooking.
Worst service ever this employe named  ANA was so rude  she Need to take some Customer classes..

I can promise you that this is the slowest Popeyes you will ever go to. Everytime I go this place is sooooooo slow. They take one order at a time and don’t take the next order until that person gets their food.

It would make more sense to take an order, then take the other orders while people wait for their food, JUST LIKE ANY OTHER FAST FOOD RESTAURANT EVER. But nope, they do things the slow way 👎🏾.

Ordered a 10 piece chicken only, but just nice in the box that was found back home. Called to complaint, one employee said sorry and said let me go back and give me a free ten piece chicken. I went back on the second day, another employee said she might only give me two prices and she thought the first employee made wrong decision and she completely disagreed with her. What a waste time by believing they are well managed organization. You should count it if you order more than ten pieces!

I was just there today 20mins ago and when I came in one of the employees sitting in the front on the phone talking loud and getting off some kinda nasty on her phone.
There’s a long line of people there were only two at the counter serving and taking orders. No smiles 🙄😐😶. I asked for the nine piece for $20 and chicken tenders with small side. Now I already waited along time to get to the counter now I got wait even longer cause the chicken was not and will not be ready for three mins. I saw my food sit there open waiting for the chicken to be ready. The young lady asked do I want dipping sauce I said yes. But what I noticed was a meal that should have cost me no more than $30 dollars cost me $40 and the bowls for the large side whe in small bowls and the one large bowl was haft filled. The young lady charged me for a 12 piece instead of what I ordered and there was no spoons, no dipping sauces,no jelly, just napkins. The cook was slamming the chicken down in bins. The young lady took two orders and never came back to me with my food until she was done with the two people behind me. I have been coming to this place for years and I have watched it go down the drain. The staff keeps changing and my food is always jacked.
Last time I was there the manager was taking my order and the whole was wrong. I had returned three times just to get the Manager to do it right my sweet tea had no sugar in it and my food was someone else’s food. The manager is a older woman who cannot keep up and the young staff needs to be either changed or trained otherwise I will not be coming to this location ever again it’s nothing like the one on Georgia ave in dc.

The worst chicken ever, I purchased the chicken tender combo thought i would get fries with it i guess not
2. It was sooooo could i couldn't eat one piece ,it taste like something that put down for long period of time not on a wormer
3. The lady that was cashing was rhe same lady servingand yes she had glubs on that she cash,and serve six person before me along with pickups that didnot change I've been to that location(west hyattsville )before tonight is my worst experience ever at a Popeye. I would never,ever go to that location again.

A quick note of thanks to the staff for making perfect food every time I order pick up. I cannot imagine our weekly NY pizza crave without the staff, especially the manager who treats me like family.

Be well, and thank you!
Stop in today at 8:00 pm, and they were closing down. 1 hour EARLY. Only one employee who obviously couldn't wait to get home. So disappointed.
They were very slow. And am a cheese loving guy, when i asked for extra cheese their reaction was not pleasing. Service does not meet price! I expect posetive attitude gir my service
The food is really good but kinda expensive. You don't really get that bang for your buck here.

So rude. If I could give 0 stars I would.
I'm never able to place an order. They close early all the time and the employees have poor hygiene. I would strongly encourage &Pizza or Chipotle. Sometimes the food is not cooked well burned or still raw dough.

Asked for a burrito only for it to all fall apart as soon as i opened it. Even heard the lady preparing it complain to the manager about how the tortillas are to small and all she did was basically mean mug me. It's stuff like this that make supporting small businesses difficult.
The food is super greasy and they are super cheap. They barely give u any food. They purposely pick the smallest pieces of meat. We are literally paying for the food not getting it for free!!!!

Food okay but Indian lady at register no manners, rude and very cheap lady. When you have a business you have to be nice to customers who help your business grow. Now they just lost two customers due to poor service. If you want to be treated with good service, don’t go here.

I was craving authentic tacos and decided to go here. I enjoyed the horchata as well! Not many places sell it so to my surprise it was very authentic and yummy. Prices are just about as chipotle but so many more options. Will def come back :)

The food was ok but the costumer service it’s terribly poor , the kitchen looks really nasty the prices are not cheap so I would not said it’s worth it , there’s better options if mexican food it’s what ur looking for.

The service is probably the best part about this place. The food is decent, but it's not great. I ordered one of their stouts and it was more watery than the thick stouts I'm accustomed to. Most of the drinks are rail and they don't have much of a selection or at least we weren't offered one. I'd go back because of the service and maybe have a different experience. I will say that, and this is very important. That the green tea shots were on point. Very happy with those.

This place has everything you could think of and want and it’s all usually pretty good! A good happy hour and nice bar vibes! I stopped in with some friends for a quick Friday night dinner.

I got the fried chicken wings with mumbo sauce and waffle fries with honey mustard. So good! I ate it all! I had their whiskey sidecar. I believe the bill altogether was around $30. Great money spent! Our server was so sweet; so upset I can’t remember her name.

I like old Dominion nice place to hang out for a drink and food.  Their buffalo wing are the best. I also like the Dominion beer draught.  The have happy hour from 4-7 pm. They also serve sushi.  The owner May very nice person. I like coming here during the daytime I personally avoid coming here in the evenings.

A friendly pub with a great happy hour, this place is wonderful for quick bites or for drinks.

I cannot in good faith recommend the margarita - it was very watered down - but the beers on tap and the food are solid pub fare, and with great, pre-COVID prices.

There's plenty of screens by the bar, and it's an excellent place to watch the games, by yourself or with friends.

Hidden off the main road I definitely had a hard time finding it. Very dive.
Waitress was nice.
I ONLY ate the waffle fries. DELICIOUS 😋
We do wish the happy hour prices were better.
I would go back. Check it out for yourself.
Delicious chicken wings. The flavors are really good! Always order from here, anytime I want to eat wings. Fast delivery and food packaging is good!

Just as good as in Singapore. Took me a long way by metro to get here from downtown but I needed to do it and it was totally worth it! I chose the flavors Hickory Smoked BBQ (boneless) and Original Hot (buffalo) with bones.

Great Sunday special! Football season is here so it took an hour for my order to be ready. (They were hustling!) fries were delicious, decent wings size. Overall very impressed! My first time here and I’d come back!

They have to have the Health Department on payroll because their drink machine is filthy. There is no way. It looks as if the actual machine hasn’t been cleaned in ages. I usually buy a bottled drink from the cvs across the street because the drink fountain machine is so yucky. Please take it apart and clean it before someone gets sick. Or better yet get a new one. Like Omg.

THEY DO NOT ANSWER THE PHONE 90% of the time! Food always correct fresh and hot. Uber eats app somehow  deleted the Hot Honey rub flavor which is my favorite but they are horrible at answering the phone
PLEASE FIX THE HOT HONEY RUB ON UBER EATS THE OPTION IS BOT THERE ANYMORE PLSSSSSS
Food was exceptionally good as Asian fast food goes. Not the best, but if you're looking for a reasonable price meal, this is one of those places. Be very hungry.
Found bugs in the food , spoke with the manager and she proceeded to get upset along with the rest of her staff. Ultimately we have spoken to the health department , it’s under investigation.

I was about to make the mistake of buying food here...but was saved by the bell. I noticed a big commotion by the line involving customers and mall police. The lady involved told me she found a COCKROACH in her food. Once I learned that I promptly got out of line and went somewhere else. Bc of this they threw the lady and her family out of the mall. I will not support this place ever again.
Very little food for the price
This food is terrible, I thought it would taste at least somewhat like panda express due to the prices being around the same but it was the complete opposite. Never going back again…

10/10
Service
Food
And environment

I'll make sure to bring my friends next time. Thank you for the food.

Getting me to comment on food is one thing. Getting me to post a photo is S-tier

My fiancé decided to take me out on a date night and he found Sushinado. The first impression I got was hardworking Asian family working and doing their best to deliver the best quality service! We took the food home, and as for my FIRST sushi burrito experience, I am very satisfied with how the Boss Mom wrap my burrito 🌯 no fell out and the quality I would say was above average but pretty good for being right around where I live. We got the #4 Tornado and the  #5 fighting terps! I call date night a success!

**Updated
We came back in the Afternoon, and got #8 Wining Vegas, #9 Dancing Twin
Tempura Shrimp Roll, Spicy Crunchy Salmon Roll, and Fried Cream Cheese Wonton. The owner is really nice and she told me that a lot people ordered the dancing twin I can say she was not wrong because I definitely enjoyed my sushi burrito.i

I have been coming here to get sushi burritos for a couple of years now and it never disappoints. I have even brought family and friends here before the pandemic and they loved it. The food is always fresh, consistent throught time and the place is very clean. The owners are always very friendly and they usually remember both my husband and I. Although we don't live as close we still try to get food from here when we can. Try it out it's so good, they have cooked options too if you don't like raw sushi amongst other dishes.

A decent sushi place that feels very genuine. Owner operated and they are both very nice. The food is maybe a little bit above average, but not at all as great as the high ratings might make you believe. Still, if you want sushi in the area this is worth a visit.

The nicest people work at this shop and the food is good too. I have ordered custom keto options and others must have as well because now they even have keto options of chicken and vegetables. If you are not doing keto the sushi burrito rolls are very good and well priced.

Upon entering the establishment it is dirty. No one greets you. I spoke and asked to place an order. When I paid for my order, I had to put the money in a box. The female took my money out the box with metal tongs. Additionally, when my order was ready, she held up the bag and nodded in my direction. I was not spoken to at all the entire time. I will not return to this location.
Never going here again!! I ordered from bonchon and there was a thick hair in my food, I couldn’t eat it.

This particular bon chon location is incredibly depressing to dine in at. The restaurant is dishoveled with take out supplies all over the dining room, there's absolutely no music playing so it's uncomfortably quiet, and they keep claiming they're "waiting for the alcohol license" since the last time they told us that 3 years ago. Come here for take out but dining in here is a straight up disappointing experience.
I love the ginger glaze chicken. There is only spicy or not, but it is overall good eating. My husband likes the kimchi.
I had to try this place after my coworkers came back raving about how good the chicken was. And YES!!! the chicken is wonderful flavorful and crispy.

Delicious spot to eat, enjoyed every bit of it. The portions are quite large so leftovers are guaranteed. I got the Veggie combo which comes with everything pictured. Only slight issue we had was during the shift switch and we were left waiting for some time. Definitely recommend this spot if you're in the college park/ route one area.

I came here and ordered the Veggie combo for 2. The food here is delicious with nice color and taste. I ate my half and I was very full, I definitely have other menu item in mind to try next time. They also provided awesome service. They also do have dine in.

It was my very first time coming here with my boyfriend. It was fantastic. The food was delicious! The lady that was at the front was friendly! The whole experience for me was awesome! Trying a different cuisine was an awesome experience!

This place is a hidden gem and I’m glad my parents told me about it. Everything from the sambusas to the doro wat to the mesir was simply amazing. There is plenty of food to go around and everything is freshly made!! I definitely will return and can’t wait to do so.

Very good food, service, and establishment. The vegetarian combination for one was $13. The dish came with large portions and all food ordered was freshly made. I love the music choice of a simple piano, it added a relaxing atmosphere.

I  usually patronize this business today i went there to cash a 10.00 lottery ticket the clerk was by himself he was busy going back in forth another customer who i know was in line to cash  a ticket also for 10.00 we both had just left 7-11 because their machine was down. He gave him his 10.00 ,  I asked were is my 10.00 he said I didn't give him the ticket, I asked him to look around maybe it failed down, there was a ticket on the counter in the other man who saw me put the ticket on the counter starting looking around the back in grabbed some ticket  from behind the counter. I called to  speak to the manager tolook at the camera  he said will be in tomorrow. I will speak with the manager tomorrow.  If you make  a mistake or you are unsure you need to own up to it?
I'm annoyed because he isn't taking responsibility for his actions. If this isn't resolved I will not patronize this business.

The prices here are okay, better with the Fuel Rewards card. Occasionally this place will fill up with cars (Thursdays!) and you have to wait a few minutes for a spot to open up or an idle car to move out of the way. The pumps normally provide receipts so you don't have to go inside. And on the whole the windshield squeegees are kept in working order.

Cashier refused to give me more than $2 in change for the air machine. After using $1.50 in the machine, I had filled 2 tires and managed to make one go flat. The clerk said there is a $2 quarter limit and refused to give me any more quarters. If you are going to try to inflate your tires or vacuum your car, make sure you bring your own quarters.
Customer Service is good but the Prices are awfully expensive!!!
This was the first place I've experienced cashier stealing money from customers, count your money always just like that 7-Eleven Riverdale, but this was before the pandemic
Great atmosphere. Mr. Greg was very friendly and such a great host. Kay was our bartender she was WONDERFUL her drinks were AMAZING. I've been recommending this place everyday since I went

Strong drinks, amazing food and great service. Steak and cheese egg rolls...bomb! Onion rings w/ spicy ranch...bomb! Friend wings...bomb! Fish Sandwich....bomb! Bartender was sweet and attentive. Played music, but was very empty. It was a random Tuesday, so it wasn't crowded at all. If you are looking for somewhere to go to mingle, this isn't it. I heard it was busy on Thursday's for karaoke, but I'm not sure.

Karokee got the party started for sure. The service was great (cute bartender-tasty drinks-respectful security-VERY accommodating). Food was okay-just okay. You have to order through their app and gratuity is automatically included. I'd return for happy hour or another karokee night.

Black,family owned. We sat at the bar, the bartender was very pleasant and welcoming for our first time there. I didn't like that my husband and I couldn't order with the bartender, we had to go thru their QR code. There were only 7 people at the bar including us two. But nevertheless the food was hot and came out quick. We ordered chx tenders and wings. Drinks were good and food was good. I will be back I want to see this place when it's packed and busy.

Food Made with Love, BOB, Kay the bartender energy and drinks are beyond measure, the whole entire staff is awesome.  TV clarity looks so live.  Greet for business meetings as well.  Love it.  Hidden Gemstone.

Ordered ahead of time for a 6:15 pick up. When I got there the doors where still locked. I stayed for about 10 minutes. However, the workers were there. When you called the phone ALL DAY phones were off the hook. This store still owes me $25.

Normally I have a good experience here. This morning he pour water in my chi tea NEVER HAD THAT DONE. Then when I ask for a cookie the lady told me they had and rung me up. Then 5mins later the guy walks up to me  saying we out of the cookie. like, check before u have me pay I wish I could take back my tip. I am very disappointed in the drink and service.

Apart from the welcoming associates, the coolest thing about Starbucks is the different coffee flavor one can choose from. The drawback is the high price, however, Starbucks' coffee taste differently plus the free wifi.
Great staff. However, this place doesn't have order ahead available most days, they close early, they close for staff meetings during work hours, most drinks are unavailable everyday. Hit and miss.
Standard Starbucks location, but as of Nov 2022 no indoor seating is available except for two high chairs in corner

I use to love Sammy's alot. I patronized them for YEARS. The son is very rude! I miss their daughter, the mother knows me. When I ask for everything as well as additional on my sandwiches,  the don't comply. I don't know what's going on with them. They really use to be my go too....and I gmfind my heading to CENTURY. TURN AROUND Sammy's.
Worst Chinese food I’ve ever tried. The General Taos chicken was like meatless rubber.

I haven't been to this place in years. At one point when I ordered from them I found mealworm..at least 12 or 13 of them inside of one of the dishes that was to contain three meats. I had this verified by Google pictures and also by a good friend who happens to know exactly what it looks like as her brother loves it. Never went there again. And never will! When I took the dish in to get my money back they said it was baby lobster! No way in hell that was baby lobster. I hope they discontinued this practice, but just the thought of it, turns me off completely from this place.

Ordered from here yesterday before the snow started. I have multiple children so my order was over $50. Got it home and went to eat it, and it was HORRIBLE!!! Tasted and smelled like the grease they cooked some of the food in was a month old VERY NASTY!!! By the time we had sat down to eat, it had already started snowing. So we had to keep the food that was fine and throw the bad food in the trash. WASTE OF MONEY!!! Won't eat there any longer or recommend this place.
This is the worst place ever, just take a look what i get last time, what is this food??? it was just a waste of money, nobody wanted to eat that, this came from that place direct to my trash

My first time experiencing Golden Krust and I am thoroughly pleased! I’m EXTREMELY picky when it comes to Jamaican restaurants— if it doesn’t taste like home cooked, then I don’t want it! EVERYTHING was delicious, from the curry chicken to the rice an peas to the plantain and cabbage! Can’t wait to try the different patties  next time! 10/10

I don't care to visit Caribbean food spots. Because most of the time the customer service is horrible! Today I had my second visit here to get some spice bun. I grabbed A large one and went to the counter to ring it up. There was an older lady at the register she rang up the spice bun. My son was there so I was a little distracted. He was having a conversation with his grandmother on the phone.  I proceeded to swipe my debit card. The machine read the card and told me to enter the card number. I said to her I must have hit something wrong. She said swipe your card again. I swiped my card two more times. By this time my Mom wanted 2 large spice buns. But she asked about freezing to Preserve freshness. I then asked the lady at the register, "Is it okay to freeze"? In A nasty mean tone,"She asked me what type of card do I have"? I told her  and flipped the card around and said, "it's just a normal debit card"! Then without her knowing I canceled the transaction and proceeded to re-swipe my card. It worked I felt relieved and was ready to go. they missed out on a $25 sale all because this Mean/rude older woman did not have more patience with me. This is a large franchise and they need to do better at this location. The food on the hot bar looks terrible!

Great service and food! It was my first time there and then staff were very helpful with walking me through the food options and their personal preferences. I had the jerk chicken, my sister had the curry chicken and my dad had the tofu vegetable dish(with curry,  not pictured) will come back here again!!!

I came in right before closing and the last veggie pattie had been sold lol I opted in for the veggie meal b/c I was so hungry.  The food was delicious and plentiful.  Just how I like it!  The cashier was very nice too btw
I Love The Golden Krust. Food is always fresh. Staff is always friendly. Best Jamaican spot in the DMV

I’ll give 2 stars because the people there are so nice and that has to count for something now a days. But this was my second time ordering the same food and while I’m eating my beef and broccoli, it tasted a little different. I look at a piece of meat that wasn’t covered in brown sauce and it was pink! Way undercooked!!!!!!

I have ordered food here for a few years. Today i had one complaint I got called a liar by the Woman who is in charge there. I waited for over a hour 6:21pm - 758pm for my food but according to her it was only 45min. The fish sandwich was cold the fries soggy and cold this was the most disappointing $19 and the worst experience I have had here. The most astonishing thing is I was only calling to let them know not even for anything free/discounted or refunded.
